---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import ApiEntry from "../../components/docs/ApiEntry.astro";
import PropsTable from "../../components/docs/PropsTable.astro";
import Example from "../../components/docs/Example.astro";
---

<DocLayout
  title="Workspace config"
  eyebrow="Where settings live"
  description="The 1.0 contract has no openpress.config.mjs. Document metadata moves to <Press> props; operational settings (deploy) live in package.json. Paths follow convention with sensible defaults."
>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>1.0 contract.</strong> <code>openpress.config.mjs</code> is deprecated. Its fields move
    to three places: <code>&lt;Press&gt;</code> props (document metadata), <code>package.json</code>
    <code>"openpress"</code> field (operational), and engine conventions (paths). Codemod in v0.10
    rewrites existing workspaces automatically.
  </div>

  <h2>The three layers</h2>

  <PropsTable
    rows={[
      {
        name: "Document metadata",
        type: "<Press> props",
        description: "<code>title</code>, <code>page</code>, <code>sources</code>, <code>theme</code>, <code>componentsDir</code>, <code>slug</code>. Display copy beyond title (subtitle / organization / author) lives in your Cover JSX, not in Press props. See <a href=\"/docs/api/press\">&lt;Press&gt;</a>.",
      },
      {
        name: "Operational",
        type: "package.json \"openpress\"",
        description: "Deploy adapter + adapter-specific config. The CLI reads this synchronously without running React, so it's the only place build-time settings can live.",
      },
      {
        name: "Paths",
        type: "Convention",
        description: 'Hardcoded engine defaults: <code>press/</code>, <code>press/theme/</code>, <code>press/components/</code>, <code>press/media/</code>, <code>public/openpress/</code>, <code>dist-react/</code>. Override only at the <code>&lt;Press&gt;</code> level (<code>theme</code>, <code>componentsDir</code>), not via a separate config file.',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Document metadata — &lt;Press&gt; props</h2>

  <p>
    See the <a href="/docs/api/press">&lt;Press&gt; page</a> for the full prop reference. The
    fields formerly in <code>openpress.config.mjs</code> map directly:
  </p>

  <PropsTable
    title="Migration from openpress.config.mjs to <Press> props"
    rows={[
      { name: "title", type: "→ <Press title>", description: "Direct move. Only required metadata prop on Press." },
      { name: "subtitle / organization / author", type: "→ Cover JSX", description: "Dropped from config — render directly in your Cover component. The codemod inlines the existing values as JSX text by default." },
      { name: "page", type: "→ <Press page>", description: "Direct move. Per-Frame override still uses <code>&lt;Frame page&gt;</code>." },
      { name: "sourceDir / mediaDir / themeDir / componentsDir", type: "→ <Press theme>, <Press componentsDir>", description: "<code>theme</code> and <code>componentsDir</code> are configurable props. <code>sourceDir</code> + <code>mediaDir</code> are now conventions, not configurable." },
      { name: "captionNumbering", type: "→ <Press captionNumbering>", description: "Direct move." },
      { name: "pdf.filename", type: "Convention", description: "Always <code>&lt;slug&gt;.pdf</code> (or <code>document.pdf</code> for single-doc workspaces). Not configurable." },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Operational — package.json "openpress"</h2>

  <ApiEntry
    name='package.json "openpress"'
    kind="config"
    status="planned"
    since="v1.0"
    importFrom={`{
  "name": "my-paper",
  "openpress": {
    "deploy": { "adapter": "...", ... }
  }
}`}
    summary="Operational config that the CLI reads sync at startup — before any React render. Deploy adapter selection lives here because openpress:deploy must know the adapter before invoking it. Most users only need to fill in the deploy block once."
  >
    <PropsTable
      title="Top-level keys"
      rows={[
        { name: "deploy", type: "DeployConfig", description: "Deploy adapter config. Required when running <code>openpress:deploy</code>; optional otherwise (CI / local dev work without it)." },
      ]}
    />

    <h3>Deploy</h3>

    <p>
      Adapter-discriminated union. Each adapter has its own required keys layered on top of the
      shared keys below.
    </p>

    <PropsTable
      title="Shared keys"
      rows={[
        { name: "adapter", type: "string", required: true, description: 'Built-in: <code>"cloudflare-pages"</code>. Planned: <code>"static-dir"</code>. Custom adapters can register their own keys.' },
        { name: "source", type: "string", default: '".deploy"', description: "Staging directory (relative to workspace root) where the deploy artifact is assembled before adapter hand-off." },
        { name: "requiresConfirmation", type: "boolean", default: "true", description: "Require <code>--confirm</code> on the command line. Disable only when the adapter has its own confirmation step." },
        { name: "commitDirty", type: "boolean", default: "false", description: "Allow deploying with uncommitted changes. Leave false in CI." },
      ]}
    />

    <h3>cloudflare-pages adapter</h3>

    <PropsTable
      rows={[
        { name: "projectName", type: "string", required: true, description: 'Cloudflare Pages project. Passed as <code>--project-name=</code> to wrangler.' },
      ]}
    />

    <Example title="Cloudflare Pages — full package.json" language="json" code={`{
  "name": "open-source-economics",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "scripts": { "build": "open-press build", "dev": "open-press dev" },
  "openpress": {
    "deploy": {
      "adapter": "cloudflare-pages",
      "source": ".deploy",
      "projectName": "open-source-economics",
      "requiresConfirmation": true
    }
  }
}`} />
  </ApiEntry>

  <h2>Paths — convention only</h2>

  <p>
    The engine hardcodes path conventions. There is intentionally no way to override these from a
    config file in v1.0 — the conventions are part of the product surface, not a tuning knob.
  </p>

  <PropsTable
    rows={[
      { name: "Content root", type: "press/", description: "Where <code>index.tsx</code> + content folders live. For multi-doc workspaces, each child <code>&lt;Press&gt;</code> nests in its own subfolder (slug)." },
      { name: "Theme", type: "press/theme/ (or per-doc)", description: 'Default <code>./theme</code> relative to the document file. Override via <code>&lt;Press theme="..."&gt;</code> if non-standard.' },
      { name: "Components", type: "press/components/", description: 'Override via <code>&lt;Press componentsDir="..."&gt;</code>.' },
      { name: "Media", type: "press/media/", description: 'Workspace-level via <code>&lt;Workspace media="..."&gt;</code>. Not per-Press configurable.' },
      { name: "Build output (engine)", type: "public/openpress/", description: "Engine writes <code>document.json</code> and synced assets here. Not configurable." },
      { name: "Build output (Vite)", type: "dist-react/", description: "Production deploy bundle. Not configurable." },
      { name: "Deploy stage", type: ".deploy/", description: "Configurable via <code>package.json openpress.deploy.source</code>; default <code>.deploy/</code>." },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Deprecated — openpress.config.mjs</h2>

  <ApiEntry
    name="openpress.config.mjs"
    kind="config"
    status="deprecated"
    since="v0.x"
    importFrom={`// openpress.config.mjs (v0.x — deprecated)
export default { title: "...", page: "a4", deploy: {...} };`}
    summary="The v0.x config file. Single-doc workspaces had this at root; nested-doc workspaces had a root pointer to press/openpress.config.mjs. Works until v1.0. v0.10 codemod migrates to the new shape."
  >
    <p>The codemod will:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Move metadata fields (<code>title</code>, <code>subtitle</code>, <code>organization</code>, <code>author</code>, <code>page</code>, <code>captionNumbering</code>) into <code>&lt;Press&gt;</code> props on the default export of <code>press/index.tsx</code>.</li>
      <li>Convert the existing <code>export const sources</code> object to an array on <code>&lt;Press sources&gt;</code>.</li>
      <li>Move <code>deploy.*</code> into <code>package.json "openpress"</code>.</li>
      <li>Drop <code>pdf.filename</code>, <code>publicDir</code>, <code>outputDir</code>, <code>documentDir</code>, and the root pointer — these become convention.</li>
      <li>Delete the <code>.mjs</code> file when the migration is clean.</li>
    </ul>
  </ApiEntry>
</DocLayout>
